            </rs>.</p>
               <p>CHARLES BOTT. I lost a handkerchief on the 1st of July, which I had in my pocket in the early part of the day; I did not miss it till the officer told me I had been robbed - this was about half-past nine o'clock, in <placeName id="t18280911-287-crimeloc1472">Berkeley-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-287-crimeloc1472" type="placeName" value="Berkeley-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-287-crimeloc1472" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-287-off1470 t18280911-287-crimeloc1472"></join> - the prisoner was taken about twenty yards from me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-287-person1585">
                  JOHN 
                  LACY
               <interp inst="t18280911-287-person1585" type="surname" value="LACY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-287-person1585" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-287-person1585" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was on duty in Piccadilly; I saw the prisoner and another follow the prosecutor and a lady: they went on, and sat down on a step- I walked down Hay-hill, and saw them again following the prosecutor; and near a gas-light, I saw the prisoner draw a handkerchief from the prosecutor, and put it under his coat; I ran over to cut him off from Lansdownpassage; he then turned round, and went round the inside of the square, near the rails - I ran and took him; the handkerchief had dropped a little before he came to the dark part of the square; I then went back to the place where I saw the handkerchief fall, but it was gone, and has not been seen since; I am quite sure the prisoner took it from the pocket.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went to get a drop of water from the pump; he came and said I had got the handkerchief. <rs id="t18280911-287-verdict1473" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-287-verdict1473" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
